    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-07-02T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-07-02T19:00:00-05:00" n="632"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d632">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.6363/2943: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-02T18:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 2, 1937—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 3—5:04 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>175. My air mail despatch No. 4892, June 17th, 1937.<note n="38"
                        xml:id="d632fn38">Not printed.</note> This morning’s <hi rend="italic">El
                        Nacional</hi> reports that a decree is in preparation providing that each
                    company or person that exploits the subsoil of Mexico in the realm of petroleum
                    is obligated in the future to pay royalties to the Federal Government in
                    accordance with article 27 of the Constitution.<note n="39" xml:id="d632fn39">
                        <ref target="frus1917#pg_951">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1917, pp. 951</ref>, <ref
                            target="frus1917#pg_955">955</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Huasteca Oil Company has been given 6 days notice by workmen of the Cerro Azul
                    fields that a general strike of its workmen in that area will be declared as a
                    result of its dismissal of 20 workmen who resorted to acts of violence against 2
                    company employees, see my despatch 4954 of June 26th.<note n="38"
                        xml:id="d632fn40">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
